# Dhall config topology — host-local / secret-bearing / generated config; never
# included in the image. The in-cluster container ships its OWN baked-in default
# Tier-0 config via docker/default-prodbox.dhall (COPYd in the Dockerfile), so the
# host's local prodbox.dhall must never leak in, and the generated *-types.dhall
# schemas are regenerated by the binary, not shipped. Sprint 1.43:
# test-secrets.dhall is the SOLE durable-secret fixture (elevated AWS creds + the
# ZeroSSL ACME EAB key) and must never enter the build context; the now-removed
# test-config(.dhall/-types.dhall) files are gone (do not re-add them here).
# NOTE: docker/default-prodbox.dhall is a DIFFERENT filename and is intentionally
# NOT excluded here — it is regenerated into the build context immediately before
# `docker build` and must remain there for the COPY to succeed.
prodbox-config.dhall
prodbox-config.json
prodbox-config-types.dhall
test-secrets.dhall
test-secrets-types.dhall
prodbox.dhall

